<td><a href="/wiki/Robert_Bulwer-Lytton,_1st_Earl_of_Lytton" title="Robert Bulwer-Lytton, 1st Earl of Lytton">Lord Lytton</a></td>
<td>12 April 1876–8 June 1880</td>
<td><a href="/wiki/Baluchistan_(Chief_Commissioners_Province)" title="Baluchistan (Chief Commissioners Province)">Baluchistan</a> established as a <a href="/wiki/Chief_Commissioner" title="Chief Commissioner">Chief Commissionership</a><br />
<a href="/wiki/Queen_Victoria" title="Queen Victoria" class="mw-redirect">Queen Victoria</a> (in absentia) proclaimed <a href="/wiki/Empress_of_India" title="Empress of India" class="mw-redirect">Empress of India</a> at <a href="/wiki/Delhi_Durbar" title="Delhi Durbar">Delhi Durbar of 1877</a>.<br />
<a href="/wiki/Great_Famine_of_1876%E2%80%9378" title="Great Famine of 1876–78">Great Famine of 1876–78</a>: 5.25 million dead; reduced relief offered at expense of <a href="/wiki/Rupee" title="Rupee">Rs.</a> 8 <a href="/wiki/Crore" title="Crore">crore</a>.<br />
Creation of Famine Commission of 1878–80 under Sir <a href="/wiki/Richard_Strachey" title="Richard Strachey">Richard Strachey</a>.<br />
Indian Forest Act of 1878<br />
<a href="/wiki/Second_Anglo-Afghan_War" title="Second Anglo-Afghan War" class="mw-redirect">Second Anglo-Afghan War</a>.</td>
