<a href="/wiki/North-Western_Provinces" title="North-Western Provinces">North-Western Provinces</a> (previously <a href="/wiki/Ceded_and_Conquered_Provinces" title="Ceded and Conquered Provinces">Ceded and Conquered Provinces</a>) and <a href="/wiki/Awadh" title="Awadh">Oudh</a> renamed <a href="/wiki/United_Provinces_of_Agra_and_Oudh" title="United Provinces of Agra and Oudh">United Provinces</a> in 1904<br />
Reorganization of Indian Universities Act (1904).<br />
Systemization of preservation and restoration of ancient monuments by <a href="/wiki/Archaeological_Survey_of_India" title="Archaeological Survey of India">Archaeological Survey of India</a> with Indian Ancient Monument Preservation Act.<br />
Inauguration of agricultural banking with Cooperative Credit Societies Act of 1904<br />
<a href="/wiki/Partition_of_Bengal_(1905)" title="Partition of Bengal (1905)">Partition of Bengal (1905)</a>; new province of <a href="/wiki/East_Bengal_and_Assam" title="East Bengal and Assam" class="mw-redirect">East Bengal and Assam</a> under a Lieutenant-Governor.</td>
