<li>James, Lawrence, <i>Raj - The Making and Unmaking of British India</i>, London, 1997, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0316640727" class="internal">ISBN 0-316-64072-7</a></li>
<li>Keay, John, <i>The Honourable Company - A History of the English East India Company</i>, <a href="/wiki/HarperCollins" title="HarperCollins">HarperCollins</a>, London, 1991, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0002175150" class="internal">ISBN 0-00-217515-0</a></li>
<li>Moorhouse, Geoffrey, <i>India Britannica</i>, Book Club Associates, UK, 1983</li>
<li>Morris, Jan, with Simon Winchester, <i>Stones of Empire - The Buildings of the Raj</i>, <a href="/wiki/Oxford_University_Press" title="Oxford University Press">Oxford University Press</a>, 1st edition 1983 (paperback edition 1986, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0192820362" class="internal">ISBN 0-19-282036-2</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Amartya_Sen" title="Amartya Sen">Sen, Amartya</a>, <i>Poverty and Famines: An Essay on Entitlements and Deprivation</i>, Oxford, Clarendon Press, 1982</li>
<li>Srivastava, H.C., <i>The History of Indian Famines from 1858-1918</i>, Sri Ram Mehra and Co., Agra, 1968</li>
